# Filament Conditional Standards

**Repo actual:** Filament no está en `composer.json`. Ignora esta regla salvo que se añada el paquete y aparezcan recursos/paneles Filament.

Apply this rule only when Filament resources are present in the repository.

## Resource Generation and Testing

- When generating a Filament resource, also create smoke tests.
- When changing a Filament resource, run relevant resource tests and update them as needed.
- Do not generate View/Infolist pages unless explicitly requested.

## Route and URL Conventions

- Prefer `ResourceClass::getUrl()` over raw `route()` calls for Filament resource links.

## Pest + Livewire Test Style

- Use `Livewire::test(ClassName::class)` in Pest tests.
- Do not rely on `livewire()` helper from optional plugins.

## Enum Usage in Filament

- If enum classes exist for model fields, use enums instead of hardcoded strings.
- Implement enum interfaces (`HasLabel`, `HasColor`, `HasIcon`) when labels/colors/icons are needed in Filament UI.
- Follow exact Filament interface return types.

## Action Authorization

- For Filament actions requiring permissions, use `->authorize('ability')`.
- Do not manually duplicate authorization with `Gate::authorize()`/`Gate::allows()` inside the same action definition.

## Filament v4 Notes

- Do not set `ignoreRecord: true` on `unique()` unless customizing behavior.
- Use `->schema()` instead of deprecated `->form()` on Actions/Filters.
- Use `->mutateDataUsing()` instead of deprecated `->mutateFormDataUsing()`.
- Use `TextEntry::make()->state()` instead of deprecated `Placeholder::make()`.
- Use `->hiddenLabel()` instead of empty `->label('')` for hidden labels.
